# Test (Open in Cursor)

When the user says **"Test"** (or "test" or "run test"), run this command in the terminal so the user can see the output:

```
npm run web:local
```

This starts the Expo web server and opens it in Cursor's Simple Browser (embedded in the IDE, not in Chrome). The server runs in the foreground; the browser opens automatically once the server is ready.
